<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 8:16PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Person,
northern Vance, northern Warren and northern Granville Counties
through 915 PM EDT...
At 815 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles west of South Hill to near Clarksville
to near Alton. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Norlina, Stovall, Middleburg, Steele Creek Marina &amp; Campground, Kerr
Lake, Wise, Lake Gaston, Southpointe And Morningstar Marinas,
Tungsten and Satterwhite Point Marina.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
